defs.name: html
defs.docs:
The main module which contents aliases to necessary items
 to create a template and implement `update` and `view` functions.
 Also this module contains declaration of `Component` trait which used
 to create own UI-components.

defs.name: ShouldRender
defs.docs: This type indicates that component should be rendered again.

defs.name: Component
defs.docs: An interface of a UI-component. Uses `self` as a model.

defs.name: Message
defs.docs: Control message type which `update` loop get.

defs.name: Properties
defs.docs:
Properties type of component implementation.
 It sould be serializable because it's sent to dynamicaly created
 component (layed under `VComp`) and must be restored for a component
 with unknown type.

defs.name: create
defs.value: fn (props: Self::Properties, context: &mut Env<CTX, Self>) -> Self
defs.docs: Initialization routine which could use a context.

defs.name: update
defs.value: fn (&mut self, msg: Self::Message, context: &mut Env<CTX, Self>) -> ShouldRender
defs.docs:
Called everytime when a messages of `Msg` type received. It also takes a
 reference to a context.

defs.name: change
defs.value: fn (&mut self, _: Self::Properties, _context: &mut Env<CTX, Self>) -> ShouldRender
defs.docs: This method called when properties changes, and once when component created.

defs.name: destroy
defs.docs: Called for finalization on the final point of the component's lifetime.

defs.name: Renderable
defs.docs: Should be rendered relative to context and component environment.

defs.name: view
defs.docs: Called by rendering loop.

defs.name: Env
defs.docs:
A reference to environment of a component (scope) which contains
 shared reference to a context and a sender to a scope's loop.

defs.name: send_back
defs.value: fn <F, IN> (&mut self, function: F) -> Callback<IN>
defs.docs: This method sends messages back to the component's loop.

defs.name: Activator
defs.docs:
Holds a reference to a scope, could put a message into the queue
 of the scope and activate processing (try borrow and call routine).

defs.name: send_message
defs.docs: Send message to a component.

defs.name: scheduler
defs.docs: Return an instance of a scheduler with a same pool of the app.

defs.docs: Holder for the element.

defs.name: InputData
defs.docs: A type representing data from `oninput` event.

defs.name: value
defs.docs:
Inserted characters. Contains value from
 [InputEvent](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/InputEvent/data).

defs.name: Value
defs.docs: Value of the element in cases of `<input>`, `<textarea>`

defs.name: Select
defs.docs:
SelectElement in case of `<select>` element. You can use one of methods of SelectElement
 to collect your required data such as: `value`, `selected_index`, `selected_indices` or
 `selected_values`. You can also iterate throught `selected_options` yourself.

defs.name: ChangeData
defs.docs:
A type representing change of value(s) of an element after committed by user
 ([onchange event](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Events/change)).

defs.name: Href
defs.docs: A bridging type for checking `href` attribute value.

defs.name: app
defs.docs:
This module contains `App` sctruct which used to bootstrap

defs.docs: Creates isolated `App` instance, but reuse the context.

defs.name: mount_to_body
defs.docs: Alias to `mount("body", ...)`.

defs.name: mount
defs.docs:
The main entrypoint of a yew program. It works similar as `program`
 function in Elm. You should provide an initial model, `update` function
 which will update the state of the model and a `view` function which
 will render the model to a virtual DOM tree.

defs.name: checked
defs.docs:
Represents `checked` attribute of
 [input](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#attr-checked).
 It exists to override standard behavior of `checked` attribute, because
 in original HTML it sets `defaultChecked` value of `InputElement`, but for reactive
 frameworks it's more useful to control `checked` value of an `InputElement`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `VTag` instance with `tag` name (cannot be changed later in DOM).

defs.name: tag
defs.docs: Returns tag of an `Element`. In HTML tags are always uppercase.

defs.docs: Add `VNode` child.

defs.name: add_classes
defs.docs:
Add classes to this virtual node. Actually it will set by
 [Element.classList.add](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/classList)
 call later.

defs.name: set_value
defs.docs:
Sets `value` for an
 [InputElement](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input).

defs.name: set_kind
defs.docs:
Sets `kind` property of an
 [InputElement](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input).
 Same as set `type` attribute.

defs.name: set_checked
defs.docs:
Sets `checked` property of an
 [InputElement](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input).
 (Not a value of node's attribute).

defs.name: add_attribute
defs.docs:
Adds attribute to a virtual node. Not every attribute works when
 it set as attribute. We use workarounds for:
 `class`, `type/kind`, `value` and `checked`.

defs.name: add_listener
defs.docs:
Adds new listener to the node.
 It's boxed because we want to keep it in a single list.
 Lates `Listener::attach` called to attach actual listener to a DOM node.

defs.docs: This module contains structs to interact with `Scope`s.

defs.name: Callback
defs.docs:
Universal callback wrapper.
 <aside class="warning">
 Use callbacks carefully, because it you call it from `update` loop
 of `Components` (even from JS) it will delay a message until next.
 Callbacks should be used from JS callbacks or `setTimeout` calls.
 </aside>
 `Rc` wrapper used to make it clonable.

 Works like common `map` method but in an opposite direction.
